  51    """An API interface for the rest only client implementation."""

  69    async def read_manifest_bytes(self, language: str = "en", /) -> bytes:
  70        """Read raw manifest SQLite database bytes response.
  71
  72        This method can be used to write the bytes to zipped file
  73        and then extract it to get the manifest content.
  74
  75        Parameters
  76        ----------
  77        language : `str`
  78            The manifest database language bytes to get.
  79
  80        Returns
  81        -------
  82        `bytes`
  83            The bytes to read and write the manifest database.
  84        """

 115    @abc.abstractmethod
 116    async def download_manifest(
 117        self,
 118        language: str = "en",
 119        name: str = "manifest",
 120        path: typing.Union[str, pathlib.Path] = ".",
 121        *,
 122        force: bool = False,
 123    ) -> None:
 124        """A helper method to download the manifest.
 125
 126        Note
 127        ----
 128        This method downloads the sqlite database and not JSON.
 129        Use `RESTInterface.download_json_manifest` for the JSON version.
 130
 131        Parameters
 132        ----------
 133        language : `str`
 134            The manifest language to download, Default is english.
 135        path: `str` | `pathlib.Path`
 136            The path to save the manifest sqlite database. Example `"D:/"`, Default is the current directory.
 137        name : `str`
 138            The manifest database file name. Default is `manifest`
 139        force : `bool`
 140            Whether to force the download. Default is `False`. However if set to true the old
 141            file will get removed and a new one will being to download.
 142
 143        Returns
 144        --------
 145        `None`
 146
 147        Raises
 148        ------
 149        `FileNotFoundError`
 150            If the manifest file exists and `force` is `False`.
 151        `ValueError`
 152            If the provided language was not recognized.
 153        """

 610    @abc.abstractmethod
 611    async def fetch_clan_members(
 612        self,
 613        clan_id: int,
 614        /,
 615        *,
 616        name: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 617        type: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.MembershipType] = enums.MembershipType.NONE,
 618    ) -> typedefs.JSONObject:
 619        """Fetch all Bungie Clan members.
 620
 621        Parameters
 622        ----------
 623        clan_id : `builsins.int`
 624            The clans id
 625
 626        Other Parameters
 627        ----------------
 628        name : `typing.Optional[str]`
 629            If provided, Only players matching this name will be returned.
 630        type : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.MembershipType]`
 631            An optional clan member's membership type.
